            {
                "comment": "Dr. Jeff is a great professor. He grades based on 3 big performance assignments and he is fairly lenient grader. He gives great feedback and genuinely wants you to do well in the class. Attendance is mandatory and the peer review workshops are really helpful. Overall, I would recommend him for ENG 100.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Best professor so far. Genuinely cares about his students and wants to engage with every person, which is rare at a school as big as UW Madison. He grades really easy so passing is easy but he gives honest - sometimes harsh - feedback because he really wants you to improve. But it never feels mean. English classes will always be a little boring. ",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Possibly the best English professor I've had. He bases this class on popular music (of any age), which makes any daunting writing task much easier. Plus, his very casual class setting and lectures make this course even more relaxed. If I see his name for another class, I would enroll in a heartbeat.",
